Title: Rentol

Description: RenTols is a web application that helps college students and 
first-time renters compare rental prices across different cities. 
Instead of searching multiple websites, users can search for rental listings in one place, view them on a map, and save cities for later.

Target Broswers:
Google Chrome
Firefox
Microsoft Edge
Safari
Chrome

Developer Manual:
How to intall:

First intall the this "npm install"

Create a .env file in the root folder with these variables:
SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url
SUPABASE_KEY=your_supabase_key
RENTCAST_KEY=your_rentcast_key
OPENCAGE_KEY=your_opencage_key

In Supabase, create a table called saved_cities with these columns:
id (int8)
city (text)
state (text)

How to Run the App:
type "node index.js" in the terminal to start the server then go to your browswer and go to http://localhost:3000

GET /geocode
Converts a city and state into coordinates using the OpenCage API. Used to move the map to the searched city.
Query parameters: city, state
Example: /geocode?city=Austin&state=TX
Returns: { lat: 30.26, lng: -97.74 }

GET /saved
Gets all saved cities from the Supabase database.
Returns an array of saved city objects with city and state.

POST /saved
Saves a city to the Supabase database.
Request body: { "city": "Austin", "state": "TX" }

Bugs:
The RentCast API has a limited data search so if it runs out you need to pay.
Map pins only appear if the listing includes coordinates from RentCast

Future Developments:
Add a delete button for saved cities
Add filters for price range and number of bedrooms